            <div class="col-sm-6 col-lg-4 mb-3">
              <h2>Ingredients</h2>
              <p class="text-muted">
                1/2 teaspoon sesame oil<br> 1 tablespoon canola oil<br> 2 pounds chicken breast,cut into 1 inch cubes<br> 4 cloves garlic, minced<br> 1 teaspoon ginger, minced<br> 1/4 cup low sodium soy sauce<br> 1/4 cup light or dark brown sugar<br>                2 tablesppons bourbon<br> 1/4 cup rice wine vinegar<br> 1 teaspoon cornstarch<br> 1 tablespoon water<br>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-6 col-lg-4 mb-3">
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <p class="text-muted">
              <ol>
                <li>Heat sesame oil and canola oil in a large skillet</li>
                <li>Add in chicken and saute until fully cooked and browned.</li>
                <li>Add in garlic and ginger and saute for 1-2 minutes. ( Add in more oil if needed)</li>
                <li>In a medium bnowl combine soy sauce, brown sugar,bourbon and rice wine vinegar.</li>
                <li>Add sauce to the chicken and bring to a simmer.Cook for 2-3 mintues.</li>
                <li>Meanwhile in a small bowl whisk together cornstarch and water.</li>
                <li>Slowly add the cornstrch mixture to the sauce and stir frequently until thickened, 2-3 minutes.</li>
                <li>If the sauce needs to thicken more and more cornstarch.</li>
                <li>Serve immediately with sesame seeds and green onions for garnish, if desired.</li>
              </ol>
        
